Product Id: Data for Newfoundland and Labrador starts in 1976. These figures are included in the Canada totals.
For calves born, refer to table 32-10-0139, for hogs, refer to table 32-10-0160 and for sheep and lambs, refer to table 32-10-0129.
Female cattle who have calved at least once, kept mainly for milk purposes.
Female cattle over a year of age, who have not yet calved, being raised mainly for milk purposes.
Female cattle over 1 year old which have never calved.
Female cattle over one year of age, who have not yet calved, being raised mainly to produce beef calves.
Excluding small numbers of heifers for slaughter and steers on dairy operations.
Farms where cattle are fed on a low energy ration such as hay or pasture.
Farms where cattle are fed a high energy ration such as grain as they are fattened for market.
Data are not available at a provincial level for the Atlantic provinces.

CANSIM Id: On August 24, 2020, a correction was made to the number of cattle, by class and farm type in New Brunswick and Ontario for the period of January 1, 2019 to July 1, 2020, in Quebec for the period of July 1, 2019 to July 1, 2020 and in Alberta for the period July 1, 2018 to July 1, 2020.
